Package org.ensor.math.analysis

This package contains code and interfaces representing Real Analysis.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IDifferentiable
    This interface represents a function which has a derivative function.
    IDifferentiableFunction
    This class defines a function over the real numbers (simulated by double precision number) which is differentiable.
    IDifferentiableT<Type>
    This interface represents a function which has a derivative function.
    IFunction
    This interface represents a function mapping R into R expressed approximately using a double precision floating point.
    IFunctionT<Type>
    This interface represents a function mapping R into <Type> expressed approximately using a double precision floating point.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ConstantFunction
    This class represents an interpolator which returns a constant value for the entire interval.
    CubicFunction
    This class represents a cubic polynomial.
    LinearFunction
    This class implements a linear function.
    QuadraticFunction
    This class represents a quadratic function.

Package org.ensor.math.analysis Description

This package contains code and interfaces representing Real Analysis. The techniques of real analysis are applicable to a wide variety of problems and specific techniques.
